- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the use of Compare&Swap, which is a low-level synchronization primitive used in programming languages.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses a system for implementing a set data structure, which could fall under this category.
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper compares the performance of their implementation to other set implementations, which could fall under this category.
